# Author: Pedro Naethe Motta (pedronaethemotta@usp.br)
# Code to generate a radiative cooling following the equations
# Ann A. Esin 1996 - HOT ONE-TEMPERATURE ACCRETION FLOWS AROUND BLACK HOLES
# Radiative cooling in function of R, Te, ne (radius, electron temperature
# and electron number density) in CGS, using texture memory in CUDA.

##############################################################################################

######################################INSTRUCTIONS############################################

1. Compile parameters_generator.c and run in order to generate three .txt files containing values for r, ne and te. Standard code provides you 100 values 
for each.

2. Compile cooling_table.c and run in order to generate a .txt file containing a table (100x100x100) with parameters r, ne, te and cooling values.

3. Compile cooling_texture.cu and run in order to use your GPU to grab this values from a texture memory location. This will help to introduce a faster 
cooling in GPU based GRMHD simulations. Inside the cooling_function() in this code, you can modify v1, v2 and v3 and checkout if it matches the data 
from the cooling_table, in order to see if the code is running smoothly and correct.



##############################################################################################
######################################END OF README##########################################
